title: Make UMAP package requirement optional with UpTrain package
body:
Currently, UpTrain requires users to install UMAP concurrently (e.g., see [this](https://github.com/uptrain-ai/uptrain/blob/main/setup.py#L48)).

However, this is not needed until some user adds a UMAP visualization requirement in the config (for example, we have such visualization requirement in the [text summarization example](https://github.com/uptrain-ai/uptrain/blob/main/examples/text_summarization/run.ipynb)).

**Issue**: We want to remove the UMAP installation requirement from UpTrain by prompting users to install UMAP independently if they have defined a UMAP check in the config.

One way to do that is "try" importing the UMAP package in this [if condition](https://github.com/uptrain-ai/uptrain/blob/main/uptrain/core/classes/managers/check_manager.py#L90), if it doesn't work, then print something like "UMAP installation not found. For UMAP visualization, please install with `pip install umap-learn`."

This is a good first issue to get started with UpTrain.

title: Change variable name from "Recommendation Bias" to "Model Bias"
body:
Recommendation bias implies that bias monitoring happens only for recommender systems. However, bias can be present in any model that makes predictions (for example, a model shortlisting applicants but prefers CVs of white males, implying racism and gender bias).

We want to change all mentions of recommendation bias, starting with [this file](https://github.com/uptrain-ai/uptrain/blob/main/uptrain/core/classes/anomalies/recommendation_bias.py), to model bias.

This is also a good first issue to get started with UpTrain.

title: Change class name from "Anomaly" to "Monitor"
body:
"Monitor" is a better name for the [Anomaly](https://github.com/uptrain-ai/uptrain/tree/main/uptrain/core/classes/anomalies) classes currently defined in the UpTrain framework. We want to replace the words Anomaly (Anomalies) with Monitor (Monitors), respectively.

This is a good first issue for users to get acquainted with the UpTrain framework.

title: Add more examples on model bias
body:
Currently, we have only one measure of [recommendation bias](https://github.com/uptrain-ai/uptrain/blob/main/uptrain/core/classes/anomalies/recommendation_bias.py) in the repository: [Popularity Bias](https://github.com/uptrain-ai/uptrain/blob/main/uptrain/core/classes/algorithms/popularity_bias.py).

It would be great to have many other measures of bias implemented in the repository, such as exposure bias, position bias, bias towards any particular feature (such as race and gender), etc. 

You can check out this [blog](https://uptrain.ai/blog/bias-in-recommendation-systems) to learn more about biases in recommendation models.

title: Add an illustration of multi-thread communication (for streamlit)
body:
Checkout out the file: https://github.com/uptrain-ai/uptrain/blob/main/uptrain/tests/test_dashboard.py

Here, streamlit dashboard runs in a separate thread and plots data that is logged in the folder `uptrain_logs`. Can we make the main thread and the streamlit thread communicate? This article might help: https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python-communicating-between-threads-set-1/

The task is to create an illustration of the threads communicating. For example, we input something from the streamlit dashboard and it prints at the python console.

body:
We currently use Streamlit for dashboarding and have a custom data-logging functionality that logs the data into CSV files to be read by streamlit. 

UpTrain config has parameters (st_logging) to turn streamlit logging on and off (https://github.com/uptrain-ai/uptrain/blob/main/uptrain/core/classes/helpers/config_handler.py)

Depending upon the config, the Log Handler class (https://github.com/uptrain-ai/uptrain/blob/main/uptrain/core/classes/logging/log_handler.py) - has functions like "add_scalars", "add_histogram", "add_alert", etc. which takes in the data and plot them onto dashboards. 

The integration will be primarily done in the Log Handler class

Grafana - https://github.com/grafana/grafana
Prometheus - https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus
